Funny, with all the steroid and HGH news over the last month or so, the
Barry Haters here have been suspiciously silent. I'd love to hear your
thoughts!

And the poster who said he could tell a 'roid or HGH user just by looking at
them, never mentioned Paul Byrd; Troy Glaus; Gary Matthews Jr.; Jose
Guillen; Matt Williams; ....

Below, an article by someone who can admit he was wrong, from yesterday's
S.F. Chronicle:

It's 'Roid Rage --- A Vote For Bonds

Scott Ostler

Sunday, November 11, 2007

Barry Bonds gets my vote.

If I have a Hall of Fame ballot when Bonds becomes eligible, assuming he
ever retires, I vote for Bonds, first time through.

I'll probably even attend his induction ceremony, which Bonds says he'll
boycott. Staring at an empty podium will be more entertaining than listening
to Barry's stream-of-semi- consciousness prattle.

A few years ago I was the first sportswriter in the country (if I don't toot
my own horn, who will?) to raise the possibility that Bonds and other
baseball greats might be kept out of the Hall of Fame because of links to
steroids.

I wrote that I would not vote for Bonds.

It takes a big man to admit when he's wrong, and I'm about seven pounds
heavier than I was back then.

There's just way too much evidence of widespread use of weapons of mass
construction. Therefore, two options:

1. Ignore the steroids questions and doubts when it's time to vote.

2. Turn Cooperstown into a flea market. Dude, this Honus Wagner plaque is
marked one buck, but his cap is kinda crooked, will you take fifty cents?

The latest 'roid villain is Matt Williams, whose dentist advised him to
floss every day and to shoot three or four different kinds of chemicals into
his butt.

If I ever get busted for steroids, remind me not to have Derrick Hall offer
my public defense. Hall, the Diamondbacks' president, defended Williams, an
announcer for the team, by saying, &quot;Matt is a stand-up guy, who without
hesitation, admitted using (growth hormone) and not liking it.&quot;

Point by point:

-- You have to stand up in order to shoot yourself in the arse.

-- Why would Williams hesitate? He and every other athlete who ordered drugs
through anti-aging clinics have known for months that they might be exposed.
Plenty of time to prepare some kind of mea culpa.

-- &quot;Not liking it&quot;? That's a defense? Sure, my client robbed the bank, Your
Honor, but he didn't enjoy it. No word from Hall on whether or not Williams
enjoyed the steroids he also reportedly ordered.
</POST>
